@node install "Installing CDB"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} Installing CDB @{ub}

 Installation is very simple thanks to Amiga Technologies official
 installer. Simply run the installer script and follow on line
 requests and instructions.

 If you want do it manually then follow these steps:

 - Copy CDB drawer where you want in your hard disk.

 PS) CDB looks for databases in "PROGDIR:data/", so no assignments are
     needed.

@endnode


@node start "Getting Started"
@endnode

@node gui "User Interface"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} User Interface @{ub}

 @{b}Shell & Workbench@{ub}

    To start program iconified simply set tooltype ICONIFY=YES in
    program icon or use ICONIFY=YES option in the CLI command line.

 @{b}Gadgets@{ub}

    @{b}Help@{ub} Leaving the mouse pointer resting on any GUI gadget will
    popup a bubble help text.

    @{b}Element gadgets@{ub} open windows with data for selected elements, data can be
    saved and printed with three gadgets available in every element window.
    User can open many windows asynchronously and operate freely without
    worrying about double selection that is igored by CDB.
    Every window provides @{b}print@{ub}, @{b}save@{ub} and @{b}save as@{ub} gadgets for printing
    and saving data.

    Synoptic table frame groups @{b}show@{ub} button and a @{b}cycle gadget@{ub} that
    allows selection out of 20 cross-reference databases. Use cycle
    gadget to make your choice and then open the correlated window.
    You can open many windows asynchronously without worrying about
    double selection that is automatically ignored by CDB.
    Every window provides @{b}print@{ub}, @{b}save@{ub} and @{b}save as@{ub} gadgets for
    printing and saving data.

    Database table frame groups @{b}show@{ub} button and a @{b}cycle gadget@{ub} that
    allows selection of databases. Use cycle gadget to make your choice
    and then open the correlated window. You can open many windows
    asynchronously without worrying about double selection that is
    automatically ignored by CDB.
    Every window provides @{b}print@{ub}, @{b}save@{ub} and @{b}save as@{ub}
    gadgets for printing and saving data.

    The "Tips" database is accessible in two distinct ways:

    It is possible to enter the element tips by simply clicking on the header of
    any element window, the header displays the element name and electronic
    configuration but it is itself a button.

    A second way is to toggle "tips" on program menu, when this menu item is checked
    every selection on the periodic table will display tips instead of element data.


 @{b}Menus@{ub}

    @{b}About CDB@{ub} Information on version of CDB, author and ARexx port.

    @{b}User Info@{ub} Information on the registered user.

    @{b}Tips@{ub} A checked menu that toggles between data and tips mode.

    @{b}MUI Prefs@{ub} Opens a window to modify CDB user interface.

    @{b}Iconify@{ub} iconifies application. This action is possible also via
    CX exchanger utility, shell, tooltypes and ARexx.

    @{b}Quit@{ub} Exits CDB.


@endnode

@node rexx "ARexx Interface"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} ARexx Interface @{ub}

 CDB include an ARexx interface. Port name consists of basename
 plus an index number. This allows multiple CDB windows to work
 in multitasking without sharing the same public message port
 for ARexx messages exchange.

 The first time CDB is run the public port name will be "CDB.1",
 but you can check the current ARexx port name just selecting
 "About CDB" menu item.

 For ARexx interprocess comunication with CDB just send commands
 to CDB ARexx port and check return variable RC for errors and
 RESULT for return values.

 Here's a little example:

 ADDRESS CDB.1        -> to select CDB ARexx port.
 OPTIONS RESULTS    -> to get results values.
 COMMAND PARAM    -> CDB internal command + parameter if needed.
 SAY RC                       -> 0=OK, 5=WARN, 10=ERROR, 20=FATAL
                                          WARN when requested operation could not be
                                          completed for memory or other problems.
 SAY RESULT              -> Check return string if needed.

 So to iconify CDB just open a shell and type:
 rx "ADDRESS CDB.1; ICONIFY" (enter)

 To get electronic configuration of Iron just enter:
 rx " ADDRESS CDB.1; OPTIONS RESULTS; GETDATA Fe 0; SAY RC; SAY RESULT" (enter)


@{b} ARexx Commands@{ub}

@{b} WinToFront@{ub} Puts CDB window to front.

@{b} WinToBack@{ub} Puts CDB window to back.

@{b} ActivateWin@{ub} Activate CDB window.

@{b} LockGUI@{ub} Locks user interface.

@{b} UnLockGUI@{ub} Unlocks user interface.

@{b} Iconify@{ub} Iconifies CDB window.

@{b} UnIconify@{ub} Uniconifies CDB window.

@{b} GetVersion@{ub} Returns complete CDB version string.

@{b} GetAuthor@{ub} Returns CDB author string.

@{b} Quit@{ub} Exits CDB without any requester.

@{b} OpenWinEl symbol/A@{ub} Opens the element window selected by symbol.

@{b} CloseWinEl symbol/A@{ub} Closes the element window selected by symbol.

@{b} SaveEl symbol/A@{ub} Saves the data for element selected by symbol.

@{b} SaveAsEl symbol/A name/A/K@{ub} Saves, with name, the data for element selected by symbol.

@{b} SaveReqEl symbol/A@{ub} Saves, with requester, the data for element selected by symbol.

@{b} PrintEl symbol/A@{ub}  Prints the data for element selected by symbol.

@{b} OpenWinTab code/N@{ub} Opens the synoptic table selected by code.

@{b} CloseWinTab code/N@{ub} Closes the synoptic table selected by code.

@{b} SaveTab code/N@{ub} Saves the synoptic table selected by code.

@{b} SaveAsTab code/N name/A/K@{ub} Saves, with name, the synoptic table selected by code.

@{b} SaveReqTab code/N@{ub} Saves, with requester, the synoptic table selected by code.

@{b} PrintTab code/N@{ub} Prints the synoptic table selected by code.

@{b} GetData symbol/A code/N@{ub} Get data selected by code for element symbol.

@{b} OpenWinDB database/N@{ub} Opens the database table selected by code.

@{b} CloseWinDB database/N@{ub} Closes the database table selected by code.

@{b} SaveDB database/N@{ub} Saves the database table selected by code.

@{b} SaveAsDB database/N name/A/K@{ub} Saves, with name, the database table selected by code.

@{b} SaveReqDB database/N@{ub} Saves, with requester, the database table selected by code.

@{b} PrintDB database/N@{ub} Prints the database table selected by code.

@{b} OpenTipsWin symbol/A@{ub} Opens the element tips window selected by symbol.

@{b} CloseTipsWin symbol/A@{ub} Closes the element tips window selected by symbol.


  @{b}Symbol@{ub} could be any standard element symbol, selection is case insensitive.

  @{b}Symbol table:@{ub}

  H He Li Be B C N O F Ne Na Mg Al Si P S Cl Ar K Ca Sc Ti V Cr Mn Fe Co Ni Cu Zn Ga
  Ge As Se Br Kr Rb Sr Y Zr Nb Mo Tc Ru Rh Pd Ag Cd In Sn Sb Te I Xe Cs Ba La Hf Ta
  W  Re Os Ir Pt Au Hg Tl Pb Bi Po At Rn Fr Ra Ac Ku Ha Ce Pr Nd Pm Sm Eu Gd Tb Dy
  Ho Er Tm Yb Lu Th Pa  U Np Pu Am Cm Bk Cf Es Fm Md No Lr

  @{b}Implemented Databases:@{ub}

    0 - Isotopes

  @{b}Codes for synoptic tables:@{ub}

   0 - Electronic Configuration
   1 - Atomic Weight
   2 - Oxidation State
   3 - Melting Point
   4 - Boiling Point
   5 - Volumic Mass
   6 - Electronegativity
   7 - Ionization Energy
   8 - Heat of Fusion
   9 - Heat of Vaporization
  10 - Thermal Conductivity
  11 - Electrical Resistivity
  12 - Specific Heat Capacity
  13 - Atomic Radius
  14 - Covalent Radius
  15 - Ionic radius
  16 - Atomic Volume
  17 - Crystal Structure
  18 - Acidic-Basic Properties
  19 - Steady Phase


@endnode


@node refs "Inside CDB"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} References for CDB @{ub}

  o Elements data and isotopes table have been extracted from

    "Tavola periodica degli elementi" by Prof. R.Barbucci
    V.Morelli Edition - Firenze, Italy.

  o Tips textfiles has been downloaded from LANL WWW archive
    (http://mwanal.lanl.gov/CST/imagemap/periodic/periodic.html)
    and then stripped of HTML tags and partially modified.
    The sources of all data are

    "CRC Handbook of Chemistry and Physics" and the
    "American Chemical Society".

  Other references from other databases will be notified
  as soon as such databases will be implemented.

@endnode



@node tech "Inside CDB"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} Inside CDB @{ub}

 @{b}CDB@{ub} has been developed with A4000 platform, SAS 6.56, MUI 3.3
 GoldED and many other tools that runs in multitasking and that
 makes great Amiga and Amiga O.S.

 CDB makes use of memory pools method in order to avoid memory
 fragmentation. No memory loss or enforcer hit has been detected.

 CDB on startup tries to load databases in "CDB:data/" and if not present
 quits and releases resources.

 Loaded databases are kept in memory with linked lists for fast and
 reliable access, this way it is possible to get a single value via ARexx.

 Other databases are not yet been implemented for technical problems
 with fonts. Chemistry databases need particular symbols that are not
 present in standard ASCII set (0-128). It could be possible to provide
 a special font with needed symbols but this would interfere with GUI
 cofigurability that, at the present time, allows font selection through
 MUI button font selector.
 I hope problem will be solved as soon as possible, it is not on top of
 my to-do list because I am working to other 3 programs and I can work only
 in my spare time.



@endnode

@node history "History"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} History@{ub}

 Many thanx to all of you for your feedback, bug-reporting and suggestions.

 @{b}Version 1.00@{ub}
  o First AMINET release.

 @{b}Version 1.01@{ub}
  o Now loading and saving to PROGDIR, no assign needed. (Albert-Jan Brouwer)
  o Removed a stupid bug on memory allocation. (Michael Currie)

 @{b}Version 1.02@{ub}
  o Added database routines.
  o Added isotopes database and 6 new ARexx commands.

 @{b}Version 1.03@{ub}
  o Element Ha was incorrect, database element.dat fixed. (Gianluca Coppo)
  o Internal minor changes. Recompiled with latest version of SAS-C.
  o New naming style for distribution: now CDB_xyy.lha, xyy=version-revision.

 @{b}Version 1.04@{ub}
  o Added 7 new elements, from 106 to 112. (Esa Haapaniemi & Ingo Paulsen)
  o Added a new database of 250Kb with history and tips on all elements.
  o Added new ARexx commands for the new database.
  o Added separate database for localized element names. (Ingo Paulsen)
  o New menu item and new tooltype LANGUAGE for selection of language.

 @{b}Version 1.05@{ub}
  o Fixed LANGUAGE tooltype bug, it didn't work.
  o Elements Ns,S,Ku,W,Pa were not correctly linked to tips database.
  o Double selection of an element tips gadget didn't work correctly.
  o Increased program stack to 50Kb.

 @{b}Version 1.06@{ub}
  o Full localization completed.
  o Removed "*.loc" files, element names have been enclosed in the catalogs.
  o Removed tooltype LANGUAGE, now CDB is locale library compliant.

 @{b}TO DO LIST@{ub}
  o Radioactive elements database.
  o Red-Ox pairs database.
  o Many other (suggested) things ...

@endnode

@node bugs "Bugs"
@font helvetica.font 11
@{b} Bugs & bug reporting @{ub}

 For bug reporting, be sure that bug is reproducible at given
 conditions. Report the exact configuration of your platform, the
 version of CDB used and of AOS (Amiga O.S.) and the circumstances
 that trigger the buggy behaviour.
 Some strange behaviour may be due to MUI library and, were it the
 case, it could be present in other MUI applications.

 Bugs could be reported via postal service or (much better)
 via e-mail to the following address:

@{b}    Stefano Peruzzi
    Via S. Dall'Arzere, 23
    I-35132 Padova - ITALY
    peru@maya.dei.unipd.it @{ub}


@{b} Possible bugs & other stuff@{ub}

 * Using MCP multi-commodity with SaveGIRPort option, could severely
   slow down CDB video refresh, causing the gadget imagery to be
   damaged when moving the sliders or using the popup gadget.

@endnode

